# Colang for the Nourish input rail.
#
# `self check input` is a BUILT-IN flow in the guardrails library: listing it
# under rails.input.flows (config.yml) runs the self_check_input prompt
# (prompts.yml) and, on a "yes" verdict, refuses and stops the turn. We do NOT
# redefine that flow here (doing so would clash with the built-in) — we only
# give the refusal a fixed message so a block costs no extra LLM generation.
# safety.py detects the stop and renders its own crisis response, so this
# wording is never shown to the user; it just needs to exist.

define bot refuse to respond
  "I'm sorry, but I can't help with that."
